# Quittance — project memory

## What this is
- **Name:** Quittance (renamed from Stellink, Oct 2025 MVP → rebranded Jul 2026).
- **Repo:** https://github.com/CemAyyildiz/Quittance
- **Stack:** Next.js 14 frontend + Express/TS backend + PostgreSQL (+ optional Redis/Bull). Freighter wallet. Stellar testnet/public.
- **Not this project:** [SustainOpen/Stellink](https://github.com/SustainOpen/Stellink) and https://stellink.vercel.app — different product (payment links / escrow). Do not confuse or merge with them.

## Product thesis (owner intent)
- Freelancer / merchant tooling: create invoice → pay on Stellar (link/QR) → auto-verify (memo + amount) → **download or email proof**.
- Proof is for the **owner** (customer, tax/official use). Settlement stays on-chain and transparent.
- Do **not** dox others: you should not infer who owns another wallet or what they did from Quittance.
- Historical legal sense of “quittance” = written discharge / payment proof you keep.

## Identity & email (locked)
- **Freighter wallet** is the only required identity for create + pay. Do not gate those flows on Google.
- **Email is optional delivery** (send invoice / send proof to the client). Prefer customer email + mailto now; SMTP/Gmail API later — still not a login gate.
- Google sign-in must not be required to create invoices or pay with Freighter.
- Canonical plan: **`PLAN.md`**. Execution checklist: `ROADMAP.md`. Do not invent alternate product paths.

## SCF rejection feedback (must address for any fund/demo push)
1. Site must be **online** for verification.
2. Provide **testnet evidence** (tx hashes + video) and clearer tech details.
3. Expand team/advisors for delivery confidence.
4. **Tighten scope:** one sharp initial user + full invoicing workflow end-to-end.

Sharp initial user (default): **freelancer invoicing a client in XLM/USDC on Stellar**.

## Current state (as of Jul 2026)
- Code last actively built ~Oct 2025; branding commit to Quittance done.
- Not deployed under Quittance yet; old Stellink Vercel slot is gone / taken by others.
- Prefer MVP path: `backend` `npm run dev:mvp` (in-memory) + `frontend` `npm run dev` when spinning up locally.
- Docs: English-only; `README.md` + `PLAN.md` / `ROADMAP.md` + env examples. No overlapping setup guides.

## Agent guardrails
- Continue the **invoice MVP**, not a SustainOpen-style payment-link rewrite.
- Prefer shipping: online demo → testnet proof → PDF/email proof workflow → dashboard history.
- Keep branding **Quittance**; never reintroduce Stellink as this app’s name.
- Do not invent unrelated features before the full invoice loop works and is demoable online.
- Follow `PLAN.md` / `ROADMAP.md` order; ask before committing; one commit = one PLAN row.
- **English only** in the repository: docs, UI strings, comments added by agents, commit messages. No Turkish in tracked files.
